95
00:08:07,967 --> 00:08:09,967
How a five year old
 got into high school?

96
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:12,133
- Oh, give it back, Blake.

97
00:08:13,467 --> 00:08:15,233
- Sure, you got it, Stretch.

98
00:08:15,233 --> 00:08:17,400
Just reach up and grab it.

99
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,233
(laughing)

100
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:22,233
Here, I'll help you out.

101
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:27,367
Nope, seems like you're
still a little short.

102
00:08:27,367 --> 00:08:29,467
- Okay, that's great.

103
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:31,267
You had your laugh for the day.

104
00:08:31,267 --> 00:08:32,500
You made me look
 like a genetic freak

105
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:35,167
and everybody thinks
 you're wonderful.

106
00:08:35,167 --> 00:08:37,567
Now just give me back my model
 sub and we'll call it a day.

107
00:08:37,567 --> 00:08:38,600
- Sure, you got it.

108
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,267
Just do one thing for me.

109
00:08:40,267 --> 00:08:41,600
- What's that?

110
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:45,767
- Say "Give me back me
Lucky Charms" (laughs).

111
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,767
But seriously Josh, how's
 the weather down there?

112
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:51,200
- Not bad, Blake.

113
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,700
How's the weather up there?

114
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:55,400
Partly to mostly stupid with
 a chance of steroids later on?

115
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:57,200
- Bad move, Tiny.

116
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,733
You wouldn't like it so
much if I crammed this

117
00:08:58,733 --> 00:09:01,867
dorky crackerjack little toy
 down your throat, would ya?

118
00:09:01,867 --> 00:09:04,333
(school bell rings)

119
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:05,700
Oops.

120
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:08,833
(shattering)

121
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:11,600
I'll get back to
you later, runt.

122
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:17,333
- Very impressive.

123
00:09:21,267 --> 00:09:23,633
- Thanks, Courtney.

124
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:26,133
- Let me guess, the
 Nautilus, right?

125
00:09:26,133 --> 00:09:29,667
From Twenty Thousand
 Leagues Under the Sea?

126
00:09:29,667 --> 00:09:31,833
It's amazing, Josh.

127
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:33,767
- Yeah, that's right.

128
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:36,733
It's a replica of the Nautilus.

129
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:38,600
But how did you know?

130
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:42,100
- How'd I know it
 was the Nautilus?

131
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:43,433
- Yeah, that.

132
00:09:43,433 --> 00:09:45,533
- Jules Verne is
 my favorite author,

133
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:47,067
and Twenty Thousand
 Leagues Under the Sea

134
00:09:47,067 --> 00:09:49,067
is my all time favorite book.

135
00:09:49,067 --> 00:09:49,900
- Really?

136
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:54,233
- I do read
occasionally, you know.

137
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:55,067
- Sorry.

138
00:09:56,067 --> 00:09:57,733
It's just...

139
00:09:57,733 --> 00:10:00,700
See, most cheerleaders are
 too busy lookin' over the top

140
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:04,000
of my head at all the tall
 jocks on the other side.

141
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,300
Do you know what I mean?

142
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,567
- Maybe you just haven't been

143
00:10:06,567 --> 00:10:09,200
meeting the right
 cheerleaders then.

144
00:10:10,033 --> 00:10:11,033
- Maybe not.

145
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:14,600
- I'll tell you what,
 my parents are going

146
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:17,433
out of town this weekend,
 and I was kind of planning

147
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:19,933
on having a party
 tonight at the Water Den.

148
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:22,367
You know, the new under 21 club.

149
00:10:22,367 --> 00:10:24,267
Do you think maybe
 you'd wanna come out?

150
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:27,000
'Cause I'd love
 to see you there.

151
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:27,833
- Really?

152
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:32,433
Well, what about your
 boyfriend Blake over there?

153
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:33,933
I mean, he'd stomp
 me into hamster mulch

154
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:35,667
if I showed up at your party.

155
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:37,267
- You're my guest, okay?

156
00:10:37,267 --> 00:10:39,633
And Rudy too if
 he wants to come.

157
00:10:39,633 --> 00:10:41,800
Blake won't give
 you any problems.

158
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:44,133
He's invited all his
 friends, so I should be able

159
00:10:44,133 --> 00:10:48,167
to invite the people I like
 hanging out with too, right?

160
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:50,600
- I don't think it's
 such a good idea.

161
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:54,133
- Well, the two of you are
 invited if you'd like to come.

162
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:57,867
- Hey Courtney,
 you comin' or what?

163
00:10:57,867 --> 00:10:59,733
- I gotta go.

164
00:10:59,733 --> 00:11:02,067
Be at the party around nine.

165
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,233
- Well?

166
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,067
- Well, it doesn't
 look like Blake

167
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:14,600
broke too much on the sub.

168
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,833
- Not that, man.

169
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:17,200
I mean the stuff over
 there with Courtney.

170
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,367
What happened?

171
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:22,700
- I think she invited us to
 a party at the Water Den.

172
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:24,133
- That's great!

173
00:11:24,133 --> 00:11:26,800
And you thought she
 wouldn't even notice you.

174
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:30,467
- Well, on the one hand,
maybe she likes me.

175
00:11:35,267 --> 00:11:37,467
And then on the other hand,

176
00:11:37,467 --> 00:11:39,967
maybe she just feels
 really sorry for me.

177
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:41,633
- Hey, don't worry, man.

178
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:44,967
How do you think I
 get most of my dates?

179
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,967
- Good morning, class.

180
00:11:47,967 --> 00:11:51,067
- [Students] Good
 morning, Mr. Duncan.

181
00:11:51,067 --> 00:11:52,533
