 for Monday's science fair.

184
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:02,433
As I gaze out on
 this vast cornucopia

185
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:05,933
of high school scientific
achievement laid out before me,

186
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:08,867
I am confident that this
 year's first prize winner

187
00:12:08,867 --> 00:12:11,167
will be someone in this class.

188
00:12:11,167 --> 00:12:12,433
Who will it be?

189
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:18,633
So, let us proceed into the
mysterious realm of the unknown,

190
00:12:18,633 --> 00:12:20,567
in the name of science.

191
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:25,367
- [Student] Okay,
 whatever, Mr. Duncan.

192
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:29,067
- Hey honey, is the
 project done yet?

193
00:12:29,067 --> 00:12:30,767
- Well, we still have
 to write the report

194
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:33,600
